                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d540">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Griscom</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-01-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 13, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 96.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The following telegraphic instruction has been
                    dispatched to-day to the American ambassadors at Vienna, Paris, Berlin, London,
                    and Rome, and to the American ministers at Brussels and Lisbon:</p>
                <p>[Text of telegram printed under circulars, <ref target="#pg_1">p. 1</ref>.]</p>
                <p>The text of the foregoing telegram is communicated to you for your information
                    and in order that you may be advised should the subject be mentioned to you by
                    the minister for foreign affairs. It is not intended for communication to the
                    government to which you are accredited, the sole object being to ascertain the
                    position of the neutral powers in this relation.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
